Gluster 3.2: Running Gluster Volume Profile Command[ Running Gluster
Volume Profile Command>>]

Using GlusterFS Volume Top and Profile commands, you can monitor
different parameters of the workload, thereby helping in capacity
planing and performance tuning tasks of the GlusterFS volume.

You can view the performance and identify bottlenecks/hotspots of each
brick of a volume. This aids system administrators to get vital
performance information whenever performance needs to be probed.

This section describes how to run GlusterFS Volume Profile and Top
Commands:

* Gluster 3.2: Running Gluster Volume Profile Command[ Running Gluster
Volume Profile Command]
* Gluster 3.2: Running Gluster Volume Top Command[ Running Gluster
Volume Top Command]

